WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:08.000
Sable Cookies

00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:10.500
Makes 65-75 pieces

00:00:10.500 --> 00:00:11.500
Ingredients

00:00:11.500 --> 00:00:13.500
225 g (1 cup) butter

00:00:13.500 --> 00:00:16.500
115 g (1 cup) powdered sugar

00:00:16.500 --> 00:00:19.500
350 g (2½ cups) flour

00:00:19.500 --> 00:00:20.700
2 egg yolks

00:00:20.700 --> 00:00:25.000
½ vanilla pod, seeds scraped out or 1 tsp vanilla extract

00:00:25.000 --> 00:00:26.000
Pinch of salt

00:00:26.000 --> 00:00:27.800
1½ tsp milk (optional)

00:00:27.800 --> 00:00:28.800
1 egg white

00:00:28.800 --> 00:00:31.500
4-5 tbsp granulated sugar

00:00:31.500 --> 00:00:32.700
Directions :

00:00:32.700 --> 00:00:44.800
Whisk the butter until smooth then add the sugar, vanilla, salt whisk until combined.

00:00:44.800 --> 00:00:50.500
Add the egg yolks 1 by 1 and whisk to combine.

00:00:50.500 --> 00:00:59.000
Sift in the flour and mix with a rubber spatula, if the dough is too dry, you can add the milk at this stage. 

00:00:59.000 --> 00:01:04.000
Bring the dough together and transfer to a work surface 

00:01:04.000 --> 00:01:09.000
then knead it with the palm of your hand 2-3 times to make it smooth.

00:01:09.000 --> 00:01:16.000
Cut the dough in half and shape each half into a 4cm diameter log 

00:01:16.000 --> 00:01:21.500
then wrap with parchment paper and chill for 1 hour at least in the fridge.

00:01:21.500 --> 00:01:27.000
Once hard enough, remove the plastic wrap and brush the log with some egg white. 

00:01:27.000 --> 00:01:33.000
Spread the granulated sugar on a piece of parchment paper and roll the dough log into the sugar

00:01:33.000 --> 00:01:37.800
then cut into ½ cm thick slices using a sharp knife.

00:01:37.800 --> 00:01:41.300
Place the biscuits on a baking tray lined with parchment paper 

00:01:41.300 --> 00:01:48.500
and bake a preheated oven at 180°C. for 10-12 minutes.

00:01:48.500 --> 00:01:51.500
Place on a wire rack to cool before serving.

